commitResults.messageBody:
CommandInput does not support the passing of application data to command
functions.

Let's make a MainManager class, that stores the application's state, and
require the creation of CommandInput a MainManager.

Passing the whole application instance will lead to cyclic dependencies
which is undesirable over the proposed method.

commitResults.messageBody:
If the user enters input fast enought, and some of them are invalid
inputs, the invalid input error message will race to be displayed with
the valid input result message. This may result in messages to be
displayed in the wrong order.

Let's make parsing a service that will be queued up to be executed in
the order that they are queued.

This synchronises the displyaing of command line result messages and
error messages from parsing.

Commands may have different ways of displaying messages such as a popup.
Allowing the commands to display the messages instead allows them to
display the message in the form that they desire.

Let's pull up the displaying logic from AppManager into the commands by
passing them the IoManager as well for execution.

Passing the command the AppManager instance might result in cyclic
dependencies.

commitResults.messageBody:
Popup is an undecorated window. Reimplementing the decorations of this
window is difficult and error prone. Unlike a window, Popup will by
default always appear on top of all others even when unfocused.

Let's use a Stage to contain the popup display instead.

This saves many lines of code and sanity.

commitResults.messageTitle: Schedule: use Schedule timeable to display
commitResults.messageBody:
There is no way to customise how a schedule for is displayed.

Let's use ScheduleTimeable instead to display schedules.

ScheduleTimeable defines methods to customise the way a schedule is
displayed. ScheduleComponent and DaySchedule are responsible for putting
the schedules on screen only and not deciding how it should be
displayed. Thus, the tasks should not be passed to those classes.
Passing the tasks will also limit the schedule graphic classes to only
work with AquaTasks which reduce resusability and abstraction.
